# v0.5.9 Change Log

**Theme**: Merge Hermes service (8103) into Agent Coordinator (8107) and rename "hermes" → "agent" across the entire codebase — consolidate all Hermes agent functionality into the Agent Coordinator, delete the Hermes service, and rename every CLI command, env var, code identifier, doc, and skill from "hermes" to "agent" so the codebase reflects the single-service architecture.

**Goal**: Move the 3 real pieces of Hermes service functionality (`/coin-requests/execute` endpoint, `TransactionService`, approval strategies + background expiration) into the Agent Coordinator. Rename `aitbc hermes *` → `aitbc agent *`, `HERMES_*` env vars → `AGENT_*`, `hermes_service.*` imports → `agent_coordinator.*`, `docs/hermes/` → `docs/agent/`, and all 3,500+ "hermes" references across the codebase. Delete the 7 mock endpoints, the Hermes service, and the 4 dead context routers in coordinator-api. Hard stop — no deprecation period. This is a **breaking change** release.

**Context**: v0.5.5 began consolidating agent messaging into the Agent Coordinator by removing `PingHandler` from Hermes, adding WebSocket `ping_handler`, and implementing auto-transfer for first-time nodes. v0.5.8 finishes the cleanup (fee fixes, dead code removal, service fixes). v0.5.9 completes the consolidation: absorb remaining Hermes functionality into the Agent Coordinator, rename everything from "hermes" to "agent", delete the Hermes service entirely, and delete the dead coordinator-api context routers.

The Hermes service has been reduced to a thin REST wrapper: 7 of its 11 endpoints are mock stubs returning hardcoded responses, and the only real endpoints (`/message`, `/health`, `/coin-requests/execute`) overlap with or can be absorbed by the Agent Coordinator, which already accesses the same SQLite DB and implements the same coin-request logic. Once the service is gone, the "Hermes" name is just leftover branding — everything is "agent" functionality in the Agent Coordinator.

**Status**: Fully implemented. All 9 sections (§1-§9) are done. The Hermes service is deleted, all functionality is in the Agent Coordinator, and the codebase-wide "hermes" → "agent" rename is complete.

